Issues.Body:
A hero with `is-fullheight-with-navbar` only accounts for a normal fixed navbar, not for a `is-spaced` navbar.

I've managed to work around it by adding this to my scss:

```scss
.is-fullheight-with-spaced-navbar {
  @extend .is-fullheight-with-navbar;
}
@media screen and (min-width: 1024px) {
  .hero.is-fullheight-with-spaced-navbar {
    min-height: calc(100vh - 5.25rem);
  }
}
```

Perhaps a class like this could be incorporated into bulma?

#### Purpose

Darker colors, specifcally $danger-dark, are not being created properly

#### How to reproduce
as outlined here https://bulma.io/documentation/customize/with-node-sass/
create a mystyles.scss with the following
```
@charset "utf-8";
$red: #af0d2e;
@import "../node_modules/bulma/sass/utilities/_all.sass";

@debug "***** $red: #{$red}"; //#af0d2e
@debug "***** $danger: #{$danger}"; //#af0d2e
@debug "***** $findDarkColor($red): #{findDarkColor($red)}"; //#ee1642
@debug "***** $danger-dark: #{$danger-dark}"; //#ee1642
```

produces

```
***** $red: #af0d2e
***** $danger: #af0d2e
***** $findDarkColor($red): #ee1642
***** $danger-dark: #ee1642
```

Where $danger is `#af0d2e` correctly being set to $red in utilities but $findDarkColor($red) produces `#ee1642` which is clearly a lighter red. 

#### What we did to fix for us

```
@charset "utf-8";
$red: #af0d2e;
// instead of importing utilities/_all.sass do each file so we can override findDarkColor
@import "~bulma/sass/utilities/initial-variables.sass";
@import "~bulma/sass/utilities/functions.sass";

//there is a problem with the bulma findDarkColor, doesn't alway darken so override.
@function findDarkColor($color) {
  @if type-of($color) == 'color' {
    @return scale-color($danger, $lightness: -20%);
  }
  @return $text-strong;
}
@import "~bulma/sass/utilities/derived-variables.sass";
@import "~bulma/sass/utilities/animations.sass";
@import "~bulma/sass/utilities/mixins.sass";
@import "~bulma/sass/utilities/controls.sass";

@debug "***** $red: #{$red}"; //#af0d2e
@debug "***** $danger: #{$danger}"; //#af0d2e
@debug "***** $findDarkColor($red): #{findDarkColor($red)}"; //#ee1642
@debug "***** $danger-dark: #{$danger-dark}"; //#ee1642
```
produces 

```
***** $red: #af0d2e
***** $danger: #af0d2e
***** $findDarkColor($red): #8c0a25
***** $danger-dark: #8c0a25
```

Where danger is `#af0d2e` and danger-darker is `#8c0a25` which is an accurate "darker" color

I think in the current version 0.8.0 is an type error.

Instead of:

`.hero .tabs ul {
    border-bottom: none;
}`

it should be:

`.hero.tabs ul {
    border-bottom: none;
}`

because otherwise the border of the tab items are set to NONE if you use them f.e. in a Card.
